The paper focuses on representation learning for source code, which is a topic that falls under software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed approach uses transfer learning from computer vision, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also evaluates the proposed approach using machine learning algorithms, indicating that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of visual patterns in source code, which may suggest that it belongs to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses natural language processing (NLP) methods as a starting point for representation learning, which may suggest that it belongs to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
